============================================================================
  SYNTHESIS
============================================================================

  Hypothesis: drain(L) has a discontinuous jump at each L = log(p)
  as a new prime enters the sieve, followed by decay. The tightest
  margin-drain gaps occur at L ~ log(p) + small_offset for each prime.

  If confirmed, the continuous-L proof problem reduces to a discrete
  bound over the countable set {log(p) : p prime}.

